<section>
    <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
      <h2 class="text-center font-semibold text-3xl py-20 hidden lg:block">What's the Difference Between Part 141 and Part 61 Training?</h2>
      <h2 class="text-center font-semibold text-2xl py-20 lg:hidden">What's the difference between <br>part 141 and part 61?</h2>
      <p class="w-4/5 lg:w-3/5 grid place-items-center pb-10 p-text">Part 141 and part 61 refer to different sections in the FAA regulations.  Part 141 is a more structured and rigorous training program that is designed for schools that are approved by the FAA to provide training under specific curricula.  Part 61, on the other hand, is a more flexible training program that allows for individualized training plans.  However due to the lack of structure, typically students may require more hours to complete part 61 training.</p>

    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row justify-center lg:items-center pl-10 lg:pl-36">
      
      
      <div class="lg:w-1/3">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-xl">Part 141</h3>
        <ul class="lg:pb-10 py-5 p-text">
          <li class="pb-2">
            <div class="flex flex-row">
              <div class="text-ideal-blue pr-3 font-extrabold">✓</div>
                Structured Curriculum
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="pb-2">
            <div class="flex flex-row">
              <div class="text-ideal-blue pr-3 font-extrabold">✓</div>
                Fewer Required Hours
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="pb-2">
            <div class="flex flex-row">
              <div class="text-ideal-blue pr-3 font-extrabold">✓</div>
